flowRoot.flowPara: 1. User sends a message on WhatsApp to the Check business account, and that message is captured by Smooch
2. There is a webhook on Smooch that sends the message to Check when a new message is sent to the WhatsApp business account
3. Check verifies API key, host and JSON payload (against JSON schema), in order to make sure that it's a valid request from Smooch
4. Check verifies if that user already sent that message, by looking for an entry in the Redis cache
4.1. Returns a message saying that the user already sent that message
5. Saves entry in Redis cache and saves two jobs to specific Sidekiq queue, in Redis too: one job to
actually process the request and another
to send a reminder to the user 20h from
5.1. Returns a message saying that the request was received successfully
6. WhatsApp Sidekiq Worker gets a job from the queue
8. Router: gets the target project based on defined rules (by language, if it looks like SPAM, etc.
7. Filters identical request made by another user
7.1. Saves annotation with this user id if another user already submitted that request and if the
10. Journalist works on the item (for example, update the language) and changes the verification status to a final one
link as a reply to the original request
7.3. / 11.2. "We checked that item as *status*. View more at <link>."
10. Bots (e.g., the Similarity Bot and the LangID Bot) add more information about the item
11.1. Saves mapping between Smooch message id and Check's project media id
11.3 Sends message saying that 24h window is over
